9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 24, L.D. 60, “An Act to Allow
10 Employees to Request Flexible Work Schedules”
11 Amend the bill in section 1 in sub-c. 13 in §879-A in subsection 1 in paragraph C in
12 subparagraph (8) in the first line (page 1, line 24 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "or"
13 Amend the bill in section 1 in sub-c. 13 in §879-A in subsection 1 in paragraph C in
14 subparagraph (9) in the last line (page 1, line 27 in L.D.) by striking out the following:
15 "employment." and inserting the following: 'employment; or'
16 Amend the bill in section 1 in sub-c. 13 in §879-A in subsection 1 in paragraph C by
17 inserting after subparagraph (9) the following:
18 '(10) Reduction in site staffing that creates less safe working conditions for other
19 employees.'
20 Amend the bill in section 1 in sub-c. 13 in §879-A in subsection 2 in the 7th line (page
21 1, line 34 in L.D.) by inserting after the following: "schedule." the following: 'If the
22 employer grants the request by the employee for a flexible work schedule, the employee
23 and employer shall mutually agree on the duration of time and the terms of that flexible
24 work schedule. The written correspondence provided to the employee indicating the
25 employer’s approval of the flexible work schedule terms and conditions must be construed
26 as a mutual agreement between the employee and employer.'
27 Amend the bill in section 1 in sub-c. 13 in §879-A in subsection 2 in the last 3 lines
28 (page 1, line 37 and page 2, lines 1 and 2 in L.D.) by striking out the following: "If the
29 employer grants the request by the employee for a flexible work schedule, the employee
30 and employer shall mutually agree on the duration of time and the terms of that flexible
31 work schedule."
32 Amend the bill by inserting after section 1 the following:
33 'Sec. 2. Appropriations and allocations. The following appropriations and
34 allocations are made.
