14 SUMMARY
1155 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, amends the bill by
1166 providing employers the authority to deny a flexible work schedule because less safe
1177 working conditions would be created by a reduction in site staffing. The amendment also
1188 requires the employer and employee to have written correspondence indicating the agreed-
1199 upon flexible work schedule.
